<subSubSection id="C31343D2FFC8FFAD6180FF6DC73EFD48" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB61059FFC8FFAD6180FF6DC4D5FF7C" blockId="4.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD6180FF6DC460FF50" bold="true" box="[199,315,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Remarks.</emphasis>
Scanning electron microscopic observations of this species from Goa (west coast of 
<collectingCountry id="F31E50C9FFC8FFAD65A3FF6DC044FF53" box="[1252,1311,187,214]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">India</collectingCountry>
) was given in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD61F3FF09C4D1FF7C" author="Chatterjee, T." box="[180,394,222,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="213 - 222" refId="ref10380" refString="Chatterjee, T. (2015 b) Scanning electron microscopic observations of Copidognathus balakrishnani Chatterjee (Acari: Halacaridae) with notes on species of the Copidognathus balakrishnani group. Acta Biologica, 22, 213 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.18276 / ab. 2015.22 - 15" type="journal article" year="2015">Chatterjee (2015b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB61059FFC8FFAD6197FED5C73EFD48" blockId="4.[151,1437,150,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">
This species belongs to ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC8FFAD60A9FED5C7F6FE98" authorityName="Chatterjee" authorityYear="2000" box="[494,685,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balakrishnani">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD60A9FED5C7F6FE98" box="[494,685,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">C. balakrishnani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group’ (
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD6257FED5C141FE98" author="Chatterjee, T. &amp; Marshall, D. J. &amp; Pesic, V." box="[784,1050,259,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="18 - 30" refId="ref11944" refString="Chatterjee, T., Marshall, D. J. &amp; Pesic, V. (2012 b) New records of Copidognathus mites (Acari: Halacaridae) from mangroves in Brunei Darussalam with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa, 3269 (1), 18 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3269.1.2" type="journal article" year="2012">
Chatterjee 
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD62C9FED5C699FE98" box="[910,962,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">et al</emphasis>
. 2012b
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD656FFED5C1ABFE98" author="Chatterjee, T." box="[1064,1264,258,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="213 - 222" refId="ref10380" refString="Chatterjee, T. (2015 b) Scanning electron microscopic observations of Copidognathus balakrishnani Chatterjee (Acari: Halacaridae) with notes on species of the Copidognathus balakrishnani group. Acta Biologica, 22, 213 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.18276 / ab. 2015.22 - 15" type="journal article" year="2015">Chatterjee 2015b</bibRefCitation>
). This group is characterized by short rostrum, small palps; areolae and costae with porose panel; PD with 4 costae; pectinate setae on tibiae I–IV: 2-2-1-1; tarsi III–IV with lateral PAS, medial PAS absent, setae ds 
<subScript id="178D121CFFC8FFAD6514FE8BC100FEEE" attach="left" box="[1107,1115,349,363]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">2</subScript>
on OC, setae ds 
<subScript id="178D121CFFC8FFAD6453FE8BC047FEEE" attach="left" box="[1300,1308,349,363]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">3</subScript>
-ds 
<subScript id="178D121CFFC8FFAD6479FE8BC01DFEEE" attach="left" box="[1342,1350,349,363]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">5</subScript>
on PD. Four species viz. 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC8FFAD601CFEB9C633FE0C" authority="Chatterjee, 2000" authorityName="Chatterjee" authorityYear="2000" box="[347,872,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balakrishnani">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD601CFEB9C7F2FE0C" box="[347,681,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Copidognathus balakrishnani</emphasis>
Chatterjee, 2000
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F31E50C9FFC8FFAD62EAFEB9C6BCFE0C" box="[941,999,367,393]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">India</collectingCountry>
(Chatterjee 2000, 2015b), 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC8FFAD6454FEB9C43DFE28" authority="Proches, 2002" authorityName="Proches" authorityYear="2002" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caloglossae">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD6454FEB9C5E7FE29" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">C. caloglossae</emphasis>
Procheş, 2002
</taxonomicName>
reported associated with the algal complex, ‘ 
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD6236FE45C148FE28" box="[881,1043,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Bostrychietum</emphasis>
’, covering the pneumatophores of mangrove 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC8FFAD6049FE61C48EFE55" box="[270,469,439,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Avicennia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marina">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD6049FE61C48EFE55" box="[270,469,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Avicennia marina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Richards Bay, Isipingo and Beachwood mangrove forests in 
<collectingRegion id="49CDDEBBFFC8FFAD65DAFE61C00BFE54" box="[1181,1360,439,465]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F31E50C9FFC8FFAD641CFE61C5BAFE70" name="South Africa" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, and at 
<collectingRegion id="49CDDEBBFFC8FFAD6070FE0DC4EDFE70" box="[311,438,475,501]" country="Mozambique" name="Inhambane" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Inhambane</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F31E50C9FFC8FFAD6086FE0DC70EFE70" box="[449,597,475,501]" name="Mozambique" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD6324FE0DC665FE70" author="Proches, S. &amp; Marshall, D. J. &amp; Ugrashen, K. &amp; Ramacharan, A." box="[611,830,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="545 - 552" refId="ref13103" refString="Proches, S., Marshall, D. J., Ugrashen, K. &amp; Ramacharan, A. (2001) Mangrove pneumatophores arthropod assemblages and temporal patterns. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the Uinted Kingdom, 81, 545 - 552. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315401004222" type="journal article" year="2001">
Procheş 
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD6383FE0DC7AEFE70" box="[708,757,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">et al</emphasis>
. 2001
</bibRefCitation>
; Procheş 2002; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD62A8FE0DC049FE70" author="Proches, S. &amp; Marshall, D. J." box="[1007,1298,475,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="1201 - 1215" refId="ref13054" refString="Proches, S. &amp; Marshall, D. J. (2002) Diversity and biogeography of southern African intertidal Acari. Journal of Biogeography, 29, 1201 - 1215. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1365 - 2699.2002.00772. x" type="journal article" year="2002">Procheş &amp; Marshall 2002</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC8FFAD6462FE0DC468FD9C" authority="Bartsch, 2003" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2003" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutarius">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD6462FE0DC0C7FE70" box="[1317,1436,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">C. lutarius</emphasis>
Bartsch, 2003
</taxonomicName>
reported among the turf of mangrove 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC8FFAD63A5FE29C609FD9D" box="[738,850,511,537]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Avicennia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marina">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD63A5FE29C609FD9D" box="[738,850,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">A. marina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the east coast of the Burrup Peninsula, Dampier, Western Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD6034FDF5C742FDB8" author="Bartsch, I." box="[371,537,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="1855 - 1877" refId="ref9071" refString="Bartsch, I. (2003 a) Mangrove halacarid fauna (Halacaridae, Acari) of the Dampier region, Western Australia, with description of five new species. Journal of Natural History, 37, 1855 - 1877. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930110089184" type="journal article" year="2003">Bartsch 2003a</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC8FFAD6319FDF5C152FDB8" authority="Bartsch, 2006" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="2006" box="[606,1033,547,573]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Copidognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhombognathoideus">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD6319FDF5C63BFDB8" box="[606,864,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">C. rhombognathoideus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD622CFDF5C152FDB8" author="Bartsch, I." box="[875,1033,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="83 - 92" refId="ref9198" refString="Bartsch, I. (2006) Copidognathines (Acari: Halacaridae) in mangroves of Singapore. I. Description of three species. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54, 83 - 92." type="journal article" year="2006">Bartsch, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
reported from algae on sediments, as well as pneumatophores and stems of mangroves in 
<collectingCountry id="F31E50C9FFC8FFAD6249FD91C6DBFDE4" box="[782,896,583,609]" name="Singapore" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Singapore</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD62C8FD91C171FDE7" author="Bartsch, I." box="[911,1066,583,610]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="83 - 92" refId="ref9198" refString="Bartsch, I. (2006) Copidognathines (Acari: Halacaridae) in mangroves of Singapore. I. Description of three species. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54, 83 - 92." type="journal article" year="2006">Bartsch 2006</bibRefCitation>
) and from algal turf growing on 
<taxonomicName id="4C096BDAFFC8FFAD61D0FDBDC441FD00" box="[151,282,619,645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhizophoraceae" genus="Rhizophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD61D0FDBDC441FD00" box="[151,282,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Rhizophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mangrove pneumatophores at Batu Marang, 
<collectingCountry id="F31E50C9FFC8FFAD6254FDBDC6B1FD00" box="[787,1002,619,645]" name="Brunei" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">Brunei Darussalam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD62BEFDBDC1A0FD03" author="Chatterjee, T. &amp; Marshall, D. J. &amp; Pesic, V." box="[1017,1275,619,646]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="18 - 30" refId="ref11944" refString="Chatterjee, T., Marshall, D. J. &amp; Pesic, V. (2012 b) New records of Copidognathus mites (Acari: Halacaridae) from mangroves in Brunei Darussalam with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa, 3269 (1), 18 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3269.1.2" type="journal article" year="2012">
Chatterjee 
<emphasis id="B97DCC4BFFC8FFAD6532FDBDC1FDFD00" box="[1141,1190,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="305">et al</emphasis>
. 2012b
</bibRefCitation>
) was assigned to this natural group (
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD60C8FD59C703FD2C" author="Chatterjee, T." box="[399,600,654,681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="213 - 222" refId="ref10380" refString="Chatterjee, T. (2015 b) Scanning electron microscopic observations of Copidognathus balakrishnani Chatterjee (Acari: Halacaridae) with notes on species of the Copidognathus balakrishnani group. Acta Biologica, 22, 213 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.18276 / ab. 2015.22 - 15" type="journal article" year="2015">Chatterjee 2015b</bibRefCitation>
). All these species were reported from low salinity zones associated with mangroves and algae (
<bibRefCitation id="EF986DA8FFC8FFAD60D5FD65C702FD48" author="Chatterjee, T." box="[402,601,690,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="305" pagination="213 - 222" refId="ref10380" refString="Chatterjee, T. (2015 b) Scanning electron microscopic observations of Copidognathus balakrishnani Chatterjee (Acari: Halacaridae) with notes on species of the Copidognathus balakrishnani group. Acta Biologica, 22, 213 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.18276 / ab. 2015.22 - 15" type="journal article" year="2015">Chatterjee 2015b</bibRefCitation>
).
